{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:job.10",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 10,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 10",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 10 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.10.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:1",
      "text": "My soul is weary of my life; I will leave my complaint upon myself; I will speak in the bitterness of my soul.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.10.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:2",
      "text": "I will say unto God, Do not condemn me; shew me wherefore thou contendest with me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.10.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:3",
      "text": "Is it good unto thee that thou shouldest oppress, that thou shouldest despise the work of thine hands, and shine upon the counsel of the wicked?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.10.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:4",
      "text": "Hast thou eyes of flesh? or seest thou as man seeth?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.10.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:5",
      "text": "Are thy days as the days of man? are thy years as man’s days,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.10.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:6",
      "text": "That thou enquirest after mine iniquity, and searchest after my sin?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.10.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:7",
      "text": "Thou knowest that I am not wicked; and there is none that can deliver out of thine hand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.10.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:8",
      "text": "Thine hands have made me and fashioned me together round about; yet thou dost destroy me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.10.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:9",
      "text": "Remember, I beseech thee, that thou hast made me as the clay; and wilt thou bring me into dust again?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.10.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:10",
      "text": "Hast thou not poured me out as milk, and curdled me like cheese?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.10.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:11",
      "text": "Thou hast clothed me with skin and flesh, and hast fenced me with bones and sinews.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.10.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:12",
      "text": "Thou hast granted me life and favour, and thy visitation hath preserved my spirit.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.10.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:13",
      "text": "And these things hast thou hid in thine heart: I know that this is with thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.10.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:14",
      "text": "If I sin, then thou markest me, and thou wilt not acquit me from mine iniquity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.10.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:15",
      "text": "If I be wicked, woe unto me; and if I be righteous, yet will I not lift up my head. I am full of confusion; therefore see thou mine affliction;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.10.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:16",
      "text": "For it increaseth. Thou huntest me as a fierce lion: and again thou shewest thyself marvellous upon me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.10.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:17",
      "text": "Thou renewest thy witnesses against me, and increasest thine indignation upon me; changes and war are against me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.10.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:18",
      "text": "Wherefore then hast thou brought me forth out of the womb? Oh that I had given up the ghost, and no eye had seen me!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.10.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:19",
      "text": "I should have been as though I had not been; I should have been carried from the womb to the grave.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.10.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:20",
      "text": "Are not my days few? cease then, and let me alone, that I may take comfort a little,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.10.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:21",
      "text": "Before I go whence I shall not return, even to the land of darkness and the shadow of death;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.10.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 10:22",
      "text": "A land of darkness, as darkness itself; and of the shadow of death, without any order, and where the light is as darkness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
